$ Graphviz: <table>

{ attribute: border

  If the `border` attribute is not specified, it defaults to `border="1"`. This is demonstrated with the following example:
  gh|about-Graphviz|/attributes/label/HTML-like/table/border.dot||

  In the created graph, the table where the `border` attribute is not specified looks like the table where it is specified to be `border="1"`:
  gh|about-Graphviz|/attributes/label/HTML-like/table/img/border.png||
}
{ attribute: color / bgcolor

  The following example tries to demonstrate the influence of the `color` and `bgcolor` attribute when applied
  to the `<table>` and `<td>` element:
  gh|about-Graphviz|/attributes/label/HTML-like/table/color.dot||

  This dot file produces:
  gh|about-Graphviz|/attributes/label/HTML-like/table/img/color.png||

}

